<TrainingDetailsVTwo ID="x68550" Name="News Article" Layout="default-training_v2.xsl"><Title type="string" label="Title" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">News Article</Title><Abstract type="string" label="Abstract" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">A news story.</Abstract><TrainingImage type="imagefile" label="Page Type Image" hidden="false" readonly="false" required="false">Internal_Use/Ingeniux_Training/Template Thumbnails/generalNewsDetail.jpg</TrainingImage><BodyCopy type="dhtml" label="Body Copy" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"><![CDATA[<h3>Proper Use</h3>
<p>Use News Articles to tell the stories of the department or office. Much like the <a href="x14924.xml">Content</a> page, news articles include a main content area for copy, images, movies, etc. News Articles also require a publication date and are indexed by the <a href="x15004.xml">News Archive</a> and <a href="x15007.xml">News Index</a> pages automatically.</p>
<p>News Articles are a powerful tool for promotion and information. They are also challenging to write well. Leverage their effectiveness by sharing them with other university newsrooms. Contact related colleges, departments, and administrative offices when you have noteworthy articles to share.</p>
<p>The <a href="x10260.xml">University Newsroom</a> is another forum for publishing your articles. Contact Andy Cargal (extension 2020, <a href="mailto:cargala@byui.edu">cargala@byui.edu</a>) and describe your article, send him a link, or request a news writeup. He has several student editors that may help refine the article as well.</p>
<p>If necessary, seek help with imagry too. Mike Lewis (ex. 2080, <a href="mailto:lewism@byui.edu">lewism@byui.edu</a>), the University Photographer, may have (or be willing to get) relevant photos pertaining to the article. Jeff Smith (ex. 7232, <a href="mailto:SmithJ@byui.edu">SmithJ@byui.edu</a>) does the same for Academic Technology Services, and should be able to help colleges, departments and other academic offices.</p>
<h3>Audience</h3>
<p>Varies</p>
<h3>Intended Authors</h3>
<p>All authors and editors.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
